tallic phases. A concise but very didactic introduction to crystallographic specifications ensures that the reader will gain a deeper understanding of the crystal structures presented in the book. The book places special emphasis on the graphical illustrations which were specifically designed to promote real insights into the structural features. Instead of having to decipher hard to distinguish graphics the reader has an eye-opening experience. A further added value is that many references to the original research publications are given which enables easy follow-up for more detailed study.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aSolid state chemistry. 4aFestkörperchemie. 4aHalbleiter. 4aKristallographie. 4aMetallorganisches Netzwerk. 7aSCIENCE / Chemistry / Inorganic.2bisacsh  aCrystallography.  aMetal-Organic Framework.  aSemiconductor.  aSolid-State Chemistry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023 Englishz978311131923008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023z9783111318660oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831106575000 cprintz978311065724140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311065729640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110657296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110657296/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  a978-3-11-131923-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-